latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you wish to study in the United Kingdom, you must be familiar with the Confirmation of Acceptance for Studies (CAS). 

Before applying for a UK Student Visa, you must first obtain a CAS. The college or institution where you have opted to study will issue you with a CAS, which is an electronic document. 
Your CAS will be valid for six months from the date of issue for student visa applications. In addition, your institution will send you a unique reference number that will match your CAS. This reference number must be mentioned on the Tier 4 visa application form. This number and a supporting document will be checked by the visa official handling your application to ensure that you have an unconditional offer from the university.
Your college will also email you the data that went into creating your CAS. This is known as a 'CAS statement'.
